  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/science/domains/biology/domains/physiology/terms/metabolism/> ;
  schema:name "Metabolism" ;
  schema:description "Metabolism is the total set of chemical reactions occurring in a living [organism](./organism.md). It is what keeps organisms alive — the continuous chemical activity that extracts energy from the environment, builds and maintains cellular structures, and disposes of waste products. An organism that stops metabolizing is dead." ;
